-- Aaron’s Extends Weeklong Rally on ‘Buy’ Report: Atlanta Mover
-- B y   B r i a n   W e l c h e r
-- 2012-01-27T19:54:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/aaron-s-unable-to-extend-weeklong-rally-atlanta-mover.html
Shares of  Aaron’s Inc. (AAN)  rose 1.85
percent to $28.12 at 2:45 p.m. in  New York , its highest price
since Oct. 27, 2011.  Cleveland-based Northcoast Research issued a ‘buy’
recommendation on Jan. 24 with a target price of $31. The
average analysts’ target price is $30.64 for the company, which
rents and sells furniture, electronics and appliances.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Welcher at   bwelcher2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
